Subject: [PATCH 04/12] feat(api): durable session streams and REST API server
 enhancements

Add durable session event streaming, session run lifecycle tracking,
and REST API enhancements for the nakov2 desktop client:

Session streams (hermes_state.py):
  - session_events table with stable item IDs and monotonic cursors
  - session_event_consumers table for consumer offset acknowledgements
  - append_session_event / list_session_events / acknowledge_consumer_offset
  - session item derivation from messages (_session_items_from_message)
  - cascade-safe event cleanup on session/message deletion

Session runs (api_server.py ResponseStore):
  - session_runs + session_run_events tables
  - create_session_run / put_session_run_event / list_session_run_events
  - mark_incomplete_session_runs_interrupted (startup recovery)

REST API endpoints (api_server.py):
  - GET /sessions (active sessions)
  - GET /sessions/:id/state (live session state with tool-call status)
  - GET /sessions/:id/items (replay-ordered session items)
  - GET /sessions/:id/events (durable event log)
  - GET /sessions/:id/events/firehose (SSE stream, resumes from offset)
  - POST /sessions/:id/events/ack (consumer offset)
  - GET/POST /sessions/:id/runs and /runs/:id/events
  - POST /responses/:id/steer, /sessions/:id/steer, /sessions/:id/halt
  - POST /sessions/:id/queue (queued user messages)
  - POST /audio/transcriptions (raw audio -> STT tool)
  - POST /responses/:id/compact (force compaction)
  - Request-scoped model override (_resolve_request_model_override)

TUI gateway (tui_gateway/server.py):
  - Live tool-call session item events via callbacks

Co-authored-by: Nako <280596805+nakoagent@users.noreply.github.com>

